<p class="lead">The content thirds pattern contains a &frac23; width column for the main content and an optional &frac13; width column for related content. There is the option of a heading above the columns and a full-width background colour.</p>

<h3>Rules for content thirds</h3>
<ul>
    <li>When using the optional heading above the columns it must use heading 2 (<code>&lt;h2&gt;</code>) and sub-headings in the content as heading 3 (<code>&lt;h3&gt;</code>).</li>
    <li>A background colour may be used, but only with one of our classes, i.e: <code>sta-grey-light</code> and <code>sta-blue</code>.</li>
    <li>The second column (&frac13;) must only contain a <a href="../navbox/index.html">navbox </a> or related content, such as text or contact information.</li>
</ul>

